Example: convert FastQ to FastA

Input (FastQ format):
@XXXXXX:57:000000000-XXXXX:1:1101:9033:1181 1:N:0:1
AGCGACGCTCAGACAGGCGTAGCCCCGGGAGGAACCCGGGGCCGCAAGTGCGTTCGAAGTGTCGATGATCAATGTGTCCTGCAATTCACATTAATTCTCGCAGCTAGCTGCGTTCTTCATCGACGCACGAGCCGAGTGATCCACCGCTAAGAATCG
+
@CCCCGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGEDGGGGGFGGEGDGGGGGGGGDFDGGGGGGGGGGGGGGDGGGGCFFGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGCGFDFGGGGGCFDGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGGDGEG:FFFGGGG<FEFG,@,?DC

Output (FastA format):
>XXXXXX:57:000000000-XXXXX:1:1101:9033:1181 1:N:0:1
AGCGACGCTCAGACAGGCGTAGCCCCGGGAGGAACCCGGGGCCGCAAGTGCGTTCGAAGTGTCGATGATCAATGTGTCCTGCAATTCACATTAATTCTCGCAGCTAGCTGCGTTCTTCATCGACGCACGAGCCGAGTGATCCACCGCTAAGAATCG

Code:

  `cat your_input.fq | awk '{if(NR%4==1) {printf(">%s\n",substr($0,2));} else if(NR%4==2) print;}' > your_output.fa`

NR: the number of records (a.k.a line number)
